OL,3,CPoliticians 'confident' for a Guernsey-
OL,4,Conly ferry service
OL,6,FBut with Guernsey sticking firm with
OL,7,FBrittany Ferries, Jersey has been
OL,8,Fstruggling to reach a solid decision,
OL,9,Fwith the most recent development
OL,10,Fseeing Condor Ferries reject a
OL,11,Fproposed seven-month extension to
OL,12,Ftheir current operating contract.
OL,14,FDeputy Neil Inder is leading
OL,15,FGuernsey's tender process and says
OL,16,Fhe's "disappointed" with Jersey not
OL,17,Fjoining them in having a single
OL,18,Fprovider.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/9
